# Mermaid Diagram Style

When creating or editing Mermaid diagrams in Markdown, use this init block as the first line inside every ` ```mermaid ` code block:

```
%%{init: {'theme': 'base', 'themeVariables': { 'fontSize': '11px', 'fontFamily': 'sans-serif' }, 'flowchart': { 'padding': 8, 'nodeSpacing': 25, 'rankSpacing': 30 }}}%%
```

**For denser diagrams** (e.g. Phase 2 file structure with many nodes), use 10px font:

```
%%{init: {'theme': 'base', 'themeVariables': { 'fontSize': '10px', 'fontFamily': 'sans-serif' }, 'flowchart': { 'padding': 8, 'nodeSpacing': 25, 'rankSpacing': 30 }}}%%
```

**Example:**

```mermaid
%%{init: {'theme': 'base', 'themeVariables': { 'fontSize': '11px', 'fontFamily': 'sans-serif' }, 'flowchart': { 'padding': 8, 'nodeSpacing': 25, 'rankSpacing': 30 }}}%%
flowchart TB
    A[Start] --> B[Process]
    B --> C[End]
```
